<plot>The film examines the present state of the fishery on the Skeena River and the many questions it faces. From the perspective of First Nations, commercial, outfitter, environmental, and government interests, we examine the socioeconomic impact of the declining fish stocks. Presenting the Skeena River as, hopefully, an inspiration and a model of how rivers, fish, and people can co-exist.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?653747</url></doc>
